node.text:
My last ride on this beautiful bike was a fast one 💨 🤩 (Unfortunately @primozroglic and @t.dumoulin had the same 🙈)
#Tokyo2020 done and dusted! I would like to thank @teambelgium and all my fans for the incredible support 🙌🏼
And now… take me home please 🙏🏼

node.text:
Mont Ventoux day in the #tdf2021 today! Every year @sportamonventoux is one of the biggest charity events to collect funds for To Walk Again. So I believe it’s the perfect day to highlight this beautiful organisation 👏🏼 

@towalkagain fights every day for one big dream. Make walking possible for everyone 👊🏼🦵🏼
Maybe one day... 💭 

In 2017, @debiesarah and I became ambassadors of this non-profit organization. Little did I know their ‘REVAlution center’ would play an important role in my comeback after my big crash in the TdF 2019.

My injury called for a slow, meticulous rehabilitation. To Walk Again truly supported me with innovative rehabilitation techniques -like Exoskeletons- to get back on track 😍

To Walk Again vzw supports everyone with a physical disability to hope and dream of an inclusive, healthy, active life. But they do not receive any subsidies from the government .To stay accessible for all, they count on donations of all of us.

Do you help realize their dream? Donate and give them the support they deserve
▶️ LINK IN BIO

4th on today’s TT, that’s far from the stage win and far from the yellow jersey 😔
I gave everything so nothing to regret 🤷🏼‍♂️ 
Thanks for the support to everyone at @jumbovisma_road 👏🏼 
See you soon 😎
